\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 128. C. biebersteinii} DC., {\i Prodr.}{\b  6}: 583 (1838). Biennial or perennial. Stems 20-70 cm, with long branches from near the base. Leaves 1- to 2-pinnatisect. Capitula solitary. Appendages mucronate or spinulose at apex. Florets pink. Pappus c. 1/3 as long as achene. 2n = 36.{\i  Cultivated and waste places. • E.C. & S.E. Europe, extending north-eastwards to N.C. Ukraine.} Al Bu Cz Hu Ju Rm Rs (C, W, K, E).
