\pard\f0\fs28   Sect. ACROCENTROIDES (DC.) Dostál. Stems herbaceous, woody at base, usually procumbent, the branches not spiny. Leaves or leaf-segments not rigid or spiny. Involucre usually ovoid; bracts with prominent veins; appendages long-cuspidate or with a long apical spine, spiny or fimbriate at the base, the lower fimbriae usually free and not forming auricles. Florets pink, purple or red.
